text: Good morning! I ran our site through the website grader tool and it flagged us on "Secure Javascript Libraries." So I went through the process <https://developers.HubSpot.com/cms/guides/jquery/upgrade|spelled out here> but the website grader is unchanged. Still tells me I have out of date javascript library. How do I know what version of the library is the "latest version."

Hi Melissa, *could you link to your website?* If you ran the first test and ran the second shortly after - there’s a chance the value for the security warning was cached. This can be manually tested however.

Hi Melissa, it appears you may have skipped a step in the guide.
> Find the jQuery checkbox and disable it.
jQuery 1.7 was still enabled in site settings.

I suggest repeating from the beginning of step 2 in the guide so you can test in step 3.
ahhh, I miss read it. THank you so much!!
